ome or in supervised after-school programs. Youth activists protest these attempts, demanding a right to the city and expanded rights of citizenship.Dangerous or Endangered? pays careful attention to the intricate connections between fears of other people's kids and fears for our own kids in order to explore the complex racial, class, and gender divides in contemporary American cities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAfrican American youthzCaliforniazOakland. 0aUrban youthzCaliforniazOakland. 4aAmerican. 4aDangerous. 4aEndangered. 4aattention. 4abetween. 4acareful. 4acities. 4aclass. 4acomplex. 4aconnections. 4acontemporary. 4adivides. 4aexplore. 4afears. 4agender. 4aintricate. 4akids. 4aorder. 4aother. 4apays. 4apeoples. 4aracial. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNYUP Backlist 2000-2013z978311070644440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814784273423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780814784273.jpg  a978-3-11-070644-4  NYUP Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK